- Check if there is no instance of MsAccess running and if so then alert and stop executing.
- Disable more shortcuts - e.g. Ctrl+O (Open File).
- Disable spawning new processes from within MsAccess (e.g. by using the Open File dialog).
- Document native WinAPI methods (P/Invoke).
- Fix: the Restore button doesn't re-enable.
- Write a documentation.
